<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 'NewsRadio' Star Arrested for Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- ``NewsRadio'' actor Andy Dick made news  
himself by getting arrested for drugs after crashing his car into a 
utility pole and trying to run away. 
</P>
<P>
	Dick, 33, who plays a bespectacled neurotic whiny reporter on  
the NBC sitcom, was released on $10,000 bond after his arrest 
Saturday, said police Officer Don Cox. 
</P>
<P>
	Dick hit the utility pole in Hollywood and then fled on foot  
about 11 a.m., Cox said. A witness chased him and detained him 
until police arrived. 
</P>
<P>
	Officers found narcotics in Dick's car, Cox said. The actor was  
scheduled to appear in court on May 25. 
</P>
<P>
	Besides ``NewsRadio,'' Dick has film credits including  
``Flashback,'' ``In the Army Now,'' ``For the Boys'' and ``Reality 
Bites.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
