<HEADLINE> J.R. Reid Fined $10,000 by NBA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- J.R. Reid of the Los Angeles Lakers was fined  
$10,000 by the NBA Sunday for a flagrant foul committed against 
Houston's Scottie Pippen in the final game of their playoff series. 
</P>
<P>
	Reid fouled Pippen with 8:39 left in the third quarter of the  
Lakers' 98-88 victory that eliminated Houston Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The fine was announced by Rod Thorn, the NBA's senior vice  
president of basketball operations, who changed the foul from a 
flagrant penalty one to a more severe flagrant penalty two. 
</P>
</TEXT>
