<HEADLINE> Hasek Pulled From Playoff Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Buffalo Sabres goalie Dominik Hasek was pulled  
after two periods on Sunday after Boston took a 4-1 lead in Game 5 
of their Eastern Conference semifinal series. 
</P>
<P>
	Hasek, who led the NHL in save percentage for the sixth  
consecutive year, had shut the Bruins out for five consecutive 
periods before he was beaten by Don Sweeney 9:01 into the first 
period. 
</P>
<P>
	Dwayne Roloson came out to start the third period and make his  
first NHL playoff appearance. 
</P>
<P>
	Hasek, the reigning NHL MVP and Vezina Trophy winner, was  
30-18-14 in the regular season and 7-1 with a 1.41 goals-against 
average in the playoffs heading into Sunday's game. 
</P>
<P>
	The Sabres entered the game with a 3-1 lead in the best-of-7  
series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
