<DOCNO> APW19990516.0051 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-16 12:41:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pippen Can't Bring Ring to Rockets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- They looked so good on paper, but another  
superstar didn't bring the Houston Rockets another championship. 
</P>
<P>
	Scottie Pippen arrived in January with six NBA championship  
rings earned in Chicago to replace the retired Clyde Drexler. 
</P>
<P>
	Hakeem Olajuwon had new spring in his aging legs after an  
off-season of intensive workouts and Charles Barkley came back from 
two off-season surgeries looking fit and charged. 
</P>
<P>
	Pippen signed a five-year, $67.5 million contract and expected  
to blend immediately with Olajuwon and Barkley, the Rockets' 
resident superstars. 
</P>
<P>
	It didn't happen.  
</P>
<P>
	Pippen reached mid-season without feeling fully acclimated to  
his new surroundings and teammates. He complained he couldn't 
perform if he didn't get the ball and finished the regular season 
with career lows in many categories, including his 14.5-point 
scoring average, the lowest since his rookie year. 
</P>
<P>
	``This was definitely a big challenge for me, coming to  
Houston,'' Pippen said. ``If we were not going to be able to win a 
playoff game or get out of the first round, it would have been very 
disappointing for me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	They did win one playoff game, but only one as the Los Angeles  
Lakers ousted them in four games. 
</P>
<P>
	Although the Rockets never got going in the lockout-shortened  
50-game schedule, they appeared to be ready to take on the Lakers. 
</P>
<P>
	Again, it didn't happen.  
</P>
<P>
	The Rockets lost Game 1 101-100 in the final seconds when Pippen  
lost the ball and rookie guard Cuttino Mobley had the final shot 
blocked by Shaquille O'Neal. They were blown out in Game 2. 
</P>
<P>
	Pippen awoke in Game 3 with a career-playoff high 37 points but  
that didn't quell his critics. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't read them, I don't know what they say,'' Pippen said.  
``Other than you guys asking me about it, I never read it. The 
important thing to Scottie Pippen is to make this team win.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In Game 4, Pippen took 23 shots, hit only six. He was 3-for-11  
from 3-point range. Although he finished with 19 points and 17 
rebounds, only three rebounds came in the second half when the 
Lakers' youth and power overcame Houston's age and experience. 
</P>
<P>
	``Scottie, Hakeem and I would have to reach to the past to match  
what we had to go against,'' Barkley said after the season-ending 
loss. ``We did the best we could.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Rockets were applauded for drafting two guards who made the  
starting lineup. Mobley became a fearless outside shooter and 
Michael Dickerson was an immediate slashing success. 
</P>
<P>
	Dickerson started all 50 regular season games and averaged 10.9  
points. Mobley averaged 9.9 points in 37 starts. But the rookies 
weren't ready for the playoff pressure. 
</P>
<P>
	During the season, Houston helped itself by sending guard  
Rodrick Rhodes to Vancouver for former Rocket Sam Mack, who added 
to the team's outside shooting capacity. 
</P>
<P>
	Houston appeared to be living up to its expectations when March  
ended. The Rockets were on a nine-game winning streak with a 22-9 
record, following a run against mostly weak teams, and were closing 
in on division-leading Utah. 
</P>
<P>
	Over the next 11 days, they lost to the Jazz twice and San  
Antonio once. They lost the home court advantage to the Lakers with 
late-season losses to NBA doormats Dallas and the Los Angeles 
Clippers, paving the way for their ouster from the playoffs in the 
first round for the second straight year. 
</P>
<P>
	``We had our ups and downs,'' coach Rudy Tomjanovich said.  
</P>
<P>
	After a loss to the Mavericks April 21, Pippen was arrested and  
charged with suspicion of driving while intoxicated. He contended 
he was innocent and the charge was dismissed for lack of evidence 
on the eve of playoff Game 4. 
</P>
<P>
	Tomjanovich has a tough off-season of work ahead of him. Pippen  
has four years remaining on his contract. Barkley is mulling 
retirement. 
</P>
<P>
	``Realistically, it is going to take a lot for me to come back  
and play,'' he said Saturday. ``I'm leaning toward retirement. That 
is what is realistic. I'm not going to play just for money. I want 
to win. It all comes down to how good this team can be.'' 
</P>
<P>
	They have a good youth base starting with Mobley and Dickerson,  
plus Bryce Drew and Othella Harrington. 
</P>
<P>
	But Olajuwon will be 37 in his 16th NBA season next year. Pippen  
will be 35 next season, his 13th. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are going to be a year older next year and I don't know  
what we can do,'' Barkley said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
