<HEADLINE>  Kiraly-Johnson Win Volleyball Event </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HUNTINGTON BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Karch Kiraly, a three-time  
Olympic gold medalist, teamed up with Adam Johnson to win the men's 
championship Sunday in the first tournament of the inaugural 
Oldsmobile Alero Beach Volleyball Series. 
</P>
<P>
	Kiraly and Johnson won their 11th professional title together by  
beating third-seeded Carl Henkel and Kevin Wong 15-9 in the finals 
at The Pier in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
	In the women's division, the top-seeded team of Lisa Arce and  
Barbra Fontana defeated the fifth-seeded team of Annett 
Buckner-Davis and Jenny Johnson-Jordan 15-12 in the finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
