<HEADLINE> Brave Act Wins Inglewood Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Brave Act, rebounding from his first  
out-of-the-money finish since 1997, overtook Lord Smith midway 
through the stretch in winning Sunday's $110,700 Inglewood Handicap 
at Hollywood Park by 3 1/2 lengths. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Goncalino Almeida and carrying 120 pounds, Brave Act  
covered 1 1-16 miles on turf in 1:39 -- just two-fifths of a second 
off the course and stakes record set by Fantastic Fellow last year. 
</P>
<P>
	The 22-10 favorite, Brave Act paid $6.40, $3.40 and $2.60.  
</P>
<P>
	``He's such a nice horse to ride because he has a big heart and  
he tries very hard every time,'' Almeida said. ``At the quarter 
pole, when I asked him, he moved fast and caught (Lord Smith) very 
easily. I think this was his best race yet.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The win was the 10th in 20 lifetime starts for Brave Act, and  
was worth $66,420, raising the career earnings of the 5-year-old 
English-bred son of Persian Bold to $724,130. 
</P>
<P>
	It was also the 16th time Brave Act has finished either first or  
second. He was coming off a fifth-place finish in the Explosive Bid 
Handicap at Louisiana's Fair Grounds, a race won by Lord Smith. 
</P>
<P>
	Lord Smith crossed the finish line 1 1/4 lengths in front of  
Expressionist in the Inglewood race and returned $4.80 and $3.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Expressionist was a half-length ahead of Such Charisma at the  
wire and paid $3.40 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Following such Charisma across the finish line in the 59th  
running of the race for 3-year-olds and up were Commitisize, 
Bouccaneer, Martiniquais and Paxos. Fabulous Guy, Kirkwall and 
Montemiro were scratched. 
</P>
<P>
	Chris Antley, who won the Preakness Stakes aboard Charasmatic in  
Baltimore on Saturday, rode two winners on Sunday's nine-race 
Hollywood Park card. 
</P>
</TEXT>
