<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brokaw: Technology Let People Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANTA FE, N.M. (AP) -- Tom Brokaw thinks technology has let  
people down, saying it has left an ``ugly scar on the face of 
history.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``An ideology designed to empower the masses became one of the  
most ruthless instruments of oppression,'' Brokaw told graduates 
during commencement at the College of Santa Fe on Saturday. ``It is 
not enough to wire the world if you short-circuit the soul. 
Technology without heart is not enough.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Brokaw, anchorman of ``NBC Nightly News,'' also urged graduates  
to ``hate hate, become color blind and take care of each other.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The author of the recent best seller ``The Greatest  
Generation,'' said that's what Americans who lived through the 
Depression and World War II fought for. 
</P>
<P>
	But now ``we have political leaders too eager to divide for  
their selfish aims rather than unify,'' Brokaw said. ``We have a 
mass media much too inclined to exploit those instincts. I wonder 
if this is what the `Greatest Generation' made all those sacrifices 
for?'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
