<HEADLINE> Gonzalez Extends Hit Streak to 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Arizona's Luis Gonzalez extended his club-record  
hitting streak to 28 games Sunday with a first-inning double off 
Pedro Astacio. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez, who has hit safely in 32 of 33 games this season,  
blooped a 2-0 pitch off the end of his bat that fell just in front 
of a sliding Larry Walker in right field. 
</P>
<P>
	Gonzalez tied Marquis Grissom for the second-longest hitting  
streak in the NL this decade. Grissom hit safely in 28 straight 
games for the Atlanta Braves in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	Hal Morris had a 29-game hitting streak for the Cincinnati Reds  
in 1996, the longest such streak this decade. Pete Rose set the NL 
mark in 1978 with a 44-game hitting streak. 
</P>
<P>
	Boston's Nomar Garciaparra and Cleveland's Sandy Alomar had  
30-game hitting streaks in 1997 and Eric Davis hit safely in 30 
consecutive games for Baltimore last season. 
</P>
